HEADWORD: dallisgrass
<hw>dallisgrass</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>a tall tufted perennial tropical American grass (<spn>Paspalum
dilatatum</spn>) naturalized as pasture and forage grass in the southern
U.S.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> paspalum, <spn>Paspalum dilatatum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
